SUMMARY:Lego Robotics for Elementary Students
DESCRIPTION:LEGO Robotics for Elementary Kids (Grades K–5) \nLEGO Robotics at Kinetic Minds introduces kids to engineering and beginner coding through hands-on building\, testing\, and problem-solving using LEGO robotics kits. \nIn this small-group\, drop-in friendly workshop\, kids work in pairs to build real robots\, program simple behaviors\, and improve their designs through guided challenges. The focus is on curiosity\, experimentation\, and learning how things work—there’s no single “right” build and no step-by-step cookie-cutter instructions. \nWorkshops are intentionally capped at a low student-to-instructor ratio to support collaboration\, confidence\, and meaningful learning. \nKids will explore:\n• Engineering and building with LEGO robotics components\n• Beginner coding concepts (motors\, sensors\, cause and effect)\n• Testing\, debugging\, and iterating designs\n• Teamwork\, communication\, and explaining ideas \nDetails:\n• 60-minute session\n• Small-group format\n• No prior experience required \nCommunity Sponsorship:\n20% of seats are reserved for community sponsorship. Families interested in sponsored spots can email info@kineticmindscreative.com\nfor details. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/lego-robotics-for-elementary-students/2026-03-28/
