SUMMARY:Imperial Brass Presents Brett Baker\, World-Renowned Trombone Virtuoso\, in Montclair
DESCRIPTION:evening of international trombone artistry with one of the brass world’s most celebrated soloists. \nImperial Brass is pleased to present an evening centered on one of the trombone world’s most celebrated voices: Brett Baker\, Solo Trombone of the renowned Cory Band of South Wales. It is a fitting program for a band whose own trombone section recently earned the Best Trombone Section award at the US Open Brass Band Championships in Michigan\, a debut appearance that also brought the band home with first place in the Challenge Section.\nA Virtuoso Comes to New Jersey\nBrett Baker needs little introduction to brass band audiences. Formerly the principal trombonist of the Black Dyke Band\, one of the oldest and most storied brass bands in the world\, Baker joined the Cory Band in late 2024\, continuing a career that has made him one of the most sought-after soloists in the brass world. Originally from the Forest of Dean in Gloucestershire\, he was encouraged to play trombone by his father and went on to study with some of the UK’s finest brass musicians before establishing himself on the international stage.\nOver the course of his career\, Baker has commissioned more than 100 trombone solos with both wind and brass band accompaniment. Several of those works will be featured in the Montclair program.\nThe concert also offers a rare opportunity for young players in the region. High school and university trombone students from across northern and central New Jersey will work with Baker in a masterclass during the day\, receiving direct feedback from one of the instrument’s leading voices\, before joining him on stage as a trombone ensemble at the evening concert. Baker will also perform a solo recital that afternoon at approximately 1:00 PM (subject to change)\, free and open to the public.\nThe Program\nThe evening’s program reflects Baker’s range and depth as a musician. It will include:\n• The 3rd Movement of the Nino Rota Trombone Concerto\n• A Never-Failing Friend by Erik Leidzén\n• The Word of Grace by Norman Bearcroft\n• My Heaven of Love by Edwin Franko Goldman\, arranged by Keith M. Wilkinson\nThe Montclair Salvation Army Citadel has long been home to the brass band tradition in New Jersey\, and its close\, resonant acoustics bring out the characteristic warmth in the brass sound.\nAbout Imperial Brass\nImperial Brass has delighted audiences across New Jersey for over 35 years. Founded in April 1991 by Rutgers alumni Steve Dillon and Jon Korzun\, with help from the late arranger Mark Freeh\, the band has performed across the northeast\, from Ocean Grove’s Great Auditorium to the Montclair Citadel\, playing everything from classical transcriptions and Sousa marches to jazz and popular music. The band is led by Ronald Waiksnoris\, a renowned conductor and former musical director of the New York Staff Band\, who has helped shape Imperial Brass into the competition-winning ensemble it is today.\nThe band rehearses weekly at the Presbyterian Church in Westfield\, which also serves as the home venue for its concert series.\nConcert Information\nDate: Saturday\, March 28\, 7:30 PM\nLocation: Montclair Salvation Army Citadel\, 13 Trinity Place\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\nTickets: $20 Adults | $15 Seniors | $10 Students & Children\nFamily Pack: $50 (two adults and unlimited child tickets)\nFor more information and to purchase tickets\, visit www.imperialbrass.org \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/imperial-brass-presents-brett-baker-world-renowned-trombone-virtuoso-in-montclair/
LOCATION:Montclair Salvation Army\, 13 Trinity Pl\, Montclair NJ\, 07042\, 13 Trinity Place\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Live Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairlocal.news/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Baker-poster-8.5-x-11-1.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Imperial Brass":MAILTO:mail@imperialbrass.org
END:VEVENT
