SUMMARY:Lunatic Fringe Comedy Show!
DESCRIPTION:Lunatic Fringe\, New Jersey’s longest running improv troupe\, continues its 29th season with a show at the Glen Ridge Train Station (Community Center) at 8 p.m. on December 13th.\nThe group uses music and audience suggestions to create a show that’s different every time\, but always funny – and always apolitical!\nIt’s not deep. It’s rarely thought-provoking. It’s just funny!\nLunatic Fringe performers include Director Deb Maclean\, Paul Murphy\, Gary Van Lieu and guest star Tommy Vorsteg!. Markus Hauck improvises on piano.\nThe show is suitable for older children\, and you are welcome to bring your own refreshments.\nTickets are still only $12 at the door\, but with a reservation\, admission is only $10. Cash only. For reservations\, call (973) 429-1527.\nCheck out our article in NJ Monthly! https://njmonthly.com/articles/arts-entertainment/lunatic-fringe-wacky-nj-improv-group-centers-audience-suggestions/ \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/lunatic-fringe-comedy-show/2026-03-28/
LOCATION:Glen Ridge Train Station Performance Space\, 228 Ridgewood Ave.\, Glen Ridge\, 07028\, United States
CATEGORIES:General Events
